  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Agile Startup Development Process is a lightweight and agile software development process specifically tailored to suit&#xD;
    the startup lifecycle. The process is based on Lean Startup methodology introduced by Eric Ries.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It outlines the mandatory tasks, roles and artifacts required for successfully establishing a startup company and the&#xD;
    supporting development process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The process covers three steps of startup lifecycle:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Problem Validation - to ensure that the problem is viable and worth solving&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Market Validation - to ensure that there exist customers willing to use and pay for the product or service created&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Product Validation - to ensure that the product and service created provides maximal usefulness for the customer.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
The process does not cover the scaling phase of the lifecycle.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
